<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Absolutely positioned, replaced elements with percentage height</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#abs-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify absolutely positioned replaced elements with percentage intrinsic height resolves based on the containing block height." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                position: relative;
                height: 1in;
            }
            #d2
            {
                position: absolute;
                left: 150px;
                background: green;
                height: 0.5in;
                width: 145px;
            }
            img
            {
                position: absolute;
                height: 50%;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if blue box and the green box are the same height.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <img alt="blue 15 x 15" src="../../../Support/blue15x15.png" />
            <div id="d2"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>